ls you just need to grow your business.\r\n\r\nImagine having the ability to view client history, edit accounts, reply to emails, interact with clients, and convert leads and lots more. In a silk , simple interfaces that shows you neatly the data you collect about your customers, so you will be able to target certain needs and products for them more strategically, meaning a platform like this will definitely save you time and increase your sales productivity.\r\n\r\n</section>','Drop #9: As Simple as your Inbox','','inherit','open','open','','42-revision-v1','','','2014-12-15 20:51:27','2014-12-15 20:51:27','',42,'http://blog.iogrow.com/42-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(48,1,'2014-12-15 20:51:42','2014-12-15 20:51:42','<h1 class=\"post-title\"><img class=\"aligncenter size-full wp-image-44\" src=\"http://blog.iogrow.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/minimal-desktop-wallpaper-simple-is-beautiful.png\" alt=\"minimal-desktop-wallpaper-simple-is-beautiful\" width=\"1299\" height=\"242\" /></h1>\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">The toast of CRM has always been its ability to integrate everything known about or discussed with a given customer so that whoever was interacting with him knew exactly what the history of previous conversations was and could more adroitly address his needs. Unfortunately staff members often have trouble in how to use the CRM correctly to both log and retrieve data, this is why ioGrow focuses on usability and simplicity.</section><section class=\"post-content\">We have cut the clutter out to provide a clean, fast, easy to use CRM without unnecessary features and complexities. Thus ioGrow is designed with simple, intuitive, powerful features to allow maximum efficiency while you are amused, enjoying nice and smooth.Organize all of your companys contacts, opportunities, leads, tasks and share them with the appropriate teams without redundancy and confusion.</section>\r\n<blockquote>\"You dont need a CRM that fights you; you need a CRM that just works!\"</blockquote>\r\nSimplicity is a lost feature in most available CRM platforms; meanwhile it is the Strength point of ioGrow. Stop wasting time struggling with spreadsheets or spam emails, or even using a confusing CRM software, and focus on growing your business. Using ioGrow can significantly boost your teams sales productivity and give you the basic core features and sales tools you just need to grow your business.\r\n\r\nImagine having the ability to view client history, edit accounts, reply to emails, interact with clients, and convert leads and lots more. In a silk , simple interfaces that shows you neatly the data you collect about your customers, so you will be able to target certain needs and products for them more strategically, meaning a platform like this will definitely save you time and increase your sales productivity.','Drop #9: As Simple as your Inbox','','inherit','open','open','','42-revision-v1','','','2014-12-15 20:51:42','2014-12-15 20:51:42','',42,'http://blog.iogrow.com/42-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(49,1,'2014-12-15 21:42:03','2014-12-15 21:42:03','<h1 class=\"post-title\"><img src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Aug/Screen_Shot_2014_08_31_at_11_34_03.png\" alt=\"\" /></h1>\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">Need customer support? Want to interview a potential hire or work with your far-flung team on a document? Theres a Hangout for that, says Google.\r\n\r\nIf youre not quite sure how serious ioGrow is about boosting business users, heres another indication that it is: ioGrow has Hangout button on both contact and lead pages, to start instant messaging or video chat with a specific contact or lead or a bunch of them.\r\n\r\nFor example, you are a customer with a problem, bam  youre in a hangout with customer support. Its basically a replacement to the live chat buttons you see on most web sites these days, but with video.\r\n<blockquote>\"Making Hangouts ubiquitous can enhance collaboration, customer service, employee recruitment and other tasks,\" said Stephen Cho, head of Google Apps and Hangouts technology partnerships.</blockquote>\r\nWith the integration of Hangout into ioGrow, it only takes one click to launch a Hangout and your team will automatically be invited.\r\n\r\nYou can even improve customer service with the ability to quickly launch into a video Hangout with a client to resolve an issue.\r\n\r\nIt will let colleagues, partners, and customers meet face-to-face anytime, anywhere, and work more effectively together with just one click. All that without you leaving your IoGrow environment!\r\n<h4 id=\"usecases\">Use cases</h4>\r\n<h5 id=\"collaborationandprojectmanagement\">Collaboration and Project Management:</h5>\r\nTeam members collaborating on a project are now able to easily start a video Hangout from Contact or lead page\r\n<h5 id=\"salesandmarketing\">Sales and Marketing:</h5>\r\nSales reps working in ioGrow can automatically kick off a Hangout with their account team , a sales rep can start a video meeting with any customer prospect\r\n<h5 id=\"customersupport\">Customer Support:</h5>\r\nioGrow also helps support agents start a Hangout to consult with other agents and internal staff, to quickly resolve support issues.\r\n<h5 id=\"social\">Social:</h5>\r\nHangout with ioGrow facilitates both 1:1 and group Hangouts initiated by anyone in a given group\r\n\r\n</section>','Drop #10: Hangout integration','','publish','open','open','','drop-10-hangout-integration','','','2014-12-15 21:42:03','2014-12-15 21:42:03','',0,'http://blog.iogrow.com/?p=49',0,'post','',0),(50,1,'2014-12-15 21:42:03','2014-12-15 21:42:03','<h1 class=\"post-title\"><img src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Aug/Screen_Shot_2014_08_31_at_11_34_03.png\" alt=\"\" /></h1>\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">Need customer support? Want to interview a potential hire or work with your far-flung team on a document? Theres a Hangout for that, says Google.\r\n\r\nIf youre not quite sure how serious ioGrow is about boosting business users, heres another indication that it is: ioGrow has Hangout button on both contact and lead pages, to start instant messaging or video chat with a specific contact or lead or a bunch of them.\r\n\r\nFor example, you are a customer with a problem, bam  youre in a hangout with customer support. Its basically a replacement to the live chat buttons you see on most web sites these days, but with video.\r\n<blockquote>\"Making Hangouts ubiquitous can enhance collaboration, customer service, employee recruitment and other tasks,\" said Stephen Cho, head of Google Apps and Hangouts technology partnerships.</blockquote>\r\nWith the integration of Hangout into ioGrow, it only takes one click to launch a Hangout and your team will automatically be invited.\r\n\r\nYou can even improve customer service with the ability to quickly launch into a video Hangout with a client to resolve an issue.\r\n\r\nIt will let colleagues, partners, and customers meet face-to-face anytime, anywhere, and work more effectively together with just one click. All that without you leaving your IoGrow environment!\r\n<h4 id=\"usecases\">Use cases</h4>\r\n<h5 id=\"collaborationandprojectmanagement\">Collaboration and Project Management:</h5>\r\nTeam members collaborating on a project are now able to easily start a video Hangout from Contact or lead page\r\n<h5 id=\"salesandmarketing\">Sales and Marketing:</h5>\r\nSales reps working in ioGrow can automatically kick off a Hangout with their account team , a sales rep can start a video meeting with any customer prospect\r\n<h5 id=\"customersupport\">Customer Support:</h5>\r\nioGrow also helps support agents start a Hangout to consult with other agents and internal staff, to quickly resolve support issues.\r\n<h5 id=\"social\">Social:</h5>\r\nHangout with ioGrow facilitates both 1:1 and group Hangouts initiated by anyone in a given group\r\n\r\n</section>','Drop #10: Hangout integration','','inherit','open','open','','49-revision-v1','','','2014-12-15 21:42:03','2014-12-15 21:42:03','',49,'http://blog.iogrow.com/49-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(51,1,'2014-12-15 21:50:34','2014-12-15 21:50:34','<h1 class=\"post-title\"><img src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Aug/Screen_Shot_2014_08_31_at_11_43_21.png\" alt=\"\" /></h1>\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">Tasks are an important part of work that needs to be done within a specific period. They are listed in every Account, contact, leads, and opportunity and in other related records.\r\nA Task is a job, responsibility, action item, or deliverable that needs to be tracked and managed to completion.\r\n\r\nioGrow is built with a unique tasks system to increase sales and close deals more efficiently, while ensuring that tasks are completed according to schedule. You can create a task and automatically assign it to the corresponding Account, Contact, or Opportunity, with just \"@\" giving other users the ability to view status of the Task.\r\n\r\nhere is why ioGrow Task manager is great for you:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>ioGrow tasks works as a great organizer tool just type your task text and set a Reminder and Due Date.</li>\r\n	<li>Easily organize your tasks with Tags with simple drag and drop gestures.</li>\r\n	<li>Instantly assign a task to someone while writing the task itself by adding @ then the person name.</li>\r\n	<li>Keep track of your workflow and get more done by sharing your work tasks.</li>\r\n	<li>Easily reassign tasks to other users as individuals responsibilities change throughout the cycle of a Sale, Project, or Opportunity.</li>\r\n	<li>With simple to tasks sharing, ioGrow is the easiest way to collaborate and get things done faster.</li>\r\n	<li>Simple, intuitive Tasks system, you can create, assign, close, reopen and even delete tasks easily.</li>\r\n	<li>The status and progress of Tasks can be viewed by other users, driving collaboration and communication within your organization, allowing you to close deals more quickly and deliver the highest levels of customer service.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTo start using ioGrow\'s Task manager, make sure you do the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>In the ioGrow homepage, click Tasks from the left menu. You can also create a task from within a Accounts, Contacts, Leads, Opportunities and even cases by clicking the Add New Task button</li>\r\n	<li>In the Create Task card, specify the task details such as title, due date, name or email, and a reminder.</li>\r\n	<li>Click Add\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Tasks closed, only when the Status of the task is updated as closed.</li>\r\n	<li>Tasks are filtered by tags for better usability and reach.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</section>','Drop #11: Tasks','','publish','open','open','','drop-11-tasks','','','2014-12-15 21:50:34','2014-12-15 21:50:34','',0,'http://blog.iogrow.com/?p=51',0,'post','',0),(52,1,'2014-12-15 21:50:34','2014-12-15 21:50:34','<h1 class=\"post-title\"><img src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Aug/Screen_Shot_2014_08_31_at_11_43_21.png\" alt=\"\" /></h1>\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">Tasks are an important part of work that needs to be done within a specific period. They are listed in every Account, contact, leads, and opportunity and in other related records.\r\nA Task is a job, responsibility, action item, or deliverable that needs to be tracked and managed to completion.\r\n\r\nioGrow is built with a unique tasks system to increase sales and close deals more efficiently, while ensuring that tasks are completed according to schedule. You can create a task and automatically assign it to the corresponding Account, Contact, or Opportunity, with just \"@\" giving other users the ability to view status of the Task.\r\n\r\nhere is why ioGrow Task manager is great for you:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>ioGrow tasks works as a great organizer tool just type your task text and set a Reminder and Due Date.</li>\r\n	<li>Easily organize your tasks with Tags with simple drag and drop gestures.</li>\r\n	<li>Instantly assign a task to someone while writing the task itself by adding @ then the person name.</li>\r\n	<li>Keep track of your workflow and get more done by sharing your work tasks.</li>\r\n	<li>Easily reassign tasks to other users as individuals responsibilities change throughout the cycle of a Sale, Project, or Opportunity.</li>\r\n	<li>With simple to tasks sharing, ioGrow is the easiest way to collaborate and get things done faster.</li>\r\n	<li>Simple, intuitive Tasks system, you can create, assign, close, reopen and even delete tasks easily.</li>\r\n	<li>The status and progress of Tasks can be viewed by other users, driving collaboration and communication within your organization, allowing you to close deals more quickly and deliver the highest levels of customer service.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nTo start using ioGrow\'s Task manager, make sure you do the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>In the ioGrow homepage, click Tasks from the left menu. You can also create a task from within a Accounts, Contacts, Leads, Opportunities and even cases by clicking the Add New Task button</li>\r\n	<li>In the Create Task card, specify the task details such as title, due date, name or email, and a reminder.</li>\r\n	<li>Click Add\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Tasks closed, only when the Status of the task is updated as closed.</li>\r\n	<li>Tasks are filtered by tags for better usability and reach.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</section>','Drop #11: Tasks','','inherit','open','open','','51-revision-v1','','','2014-12-15 21:50:34','2014-12-15 21:50:34','',51,'http://blog.iogrow.com/51-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(53,1,'2014-12-15 22:04:14','2014-12-15 22:04:14','<p class=\"post-title\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"post-title\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Aug/Screen_Shot_2014_08_31_at_11_34_03-1.png\" alt=\"\" />Acquiring leads<span style=\"font-size: 0.875em; line-height: 1.5;\">is great, but keeping them as contacts is better, ioGrow simplfies the process of converting a lead into contact.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Click on the Lead record you intend to convert</li>\r\n	<li>In the detail view, Click Convert Button</li>\r\n	<li>In the confirmation pop-up, you can confirm by clicking Convert this Lead button.</li>\r\n	<li>You will be redirected automatically to Contact page view of the new converted lead</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 id=\"disclaimer\">Disclaimer</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Converting a lead will create a person contact and company. All documents, notes, tasks and events will be transferred. You should only convert a lead if it is qualified.</li>\r\n	<li>Lead record will no more be available in Leads page, after Lead Conversion.</li>\r\n	<li>After conversion, Contact, Account records cannot be reverted to the previous state</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</section>','Drop #12: Convert a lead','','publish','open','open','','drop-12-convert-a-lead','','','2014-12-15 22:04:14','2014-12-15 22:04:14','',0,'http://blog.iogrow.com/?p=53',0,'post','',0),(54,1,'2014-12-15 22:04:14','2014-12-15 22:04:14','<p class=\"post-title\"></p>\r\n<p class=\"post-title\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Aug/Screen_Shot_2014_08_31_at_11_34_03-1.png\" alt=\"\" />Acquiring leads<span style=\"font-size: 0.875em; line-height: 1.5;\">is great, but keeping them as contacts is better, ioGrow simplfies the process of converting a lead into contact.</span></p>\r\n\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Click on the Lead record you intend to convert</li>\r\n	<li>In the detail view, Click Convert Button</li>\r\n	<li>In the confirmation pop-up, you can confirm by clicking Convert this Lead button.</li>\r\n	<li>You will be redirected automatically to Contact page view of the new converted lead</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h4 id=\"disclaimer\">Disclaimer</h4>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Converting a lead will create a person contact and company. All documents, notes, tasks and events will be transferred. You should only convert a lead if it is qualified.</li>\r\n	<li>Lead record will no more be available in Leads page, after Lead Conversion.</li>\r\n	<li>After conversion, Contact, Account records cannot be reverted to the previous state</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</section>','Drop #12: Convert a lead','','inherit','open','open','','53-revision-v1','','','2014-12-15 22:04:14','2014-12-15 22:04:14','',53,'http://blog.iogrow.com/53-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(55,1,'2014-12-15 22:32:10','2014-12-15 22:32:10','During your business life, you will meet some new interesting people who are potential customers in future; we call these people Leads.\r\n\r\nAccording to Leads360 s analysis of 25 million data points, speed is the single most critical component to lead conversion. Conversion rates are 391% higher when the lead is called within a minute of their inquiry; 120% within two minutes; 98% in under three minutes; 62% in under 30 minutes; and 36% in under an hour.\r\n\r\nReceiving and reacting to leads in real-time is critical to maximizing conversion rates. The companies that do this best measure reaction-time-to-new leads in seconds, not hours. By doing so, they achieve the first contact advantage with prospects.\r\nIOGrow provides you with full-detailed cards about your leads; you can see their phone number, email, address and even their social links. This will help you organize and keep tracking your leads so they can be qualified smoothly.\r\n\r\nA new qualified lead means a new customer contact or account. By converting your qualified leads into contacts, you will have all the information of your leads transferred to a new customer contact card instantly.\r\n\r\nOnce a Lead is qualified and determined to be a potential sale, the Lead can be converted to a Contact. A Company Account record will be created simultaneously to store the personal information and company information.','Drop #13: Managing leads','','publish','open','open','','drop-13-managing-leads','','','2014-12-16 12:55:39','2014-12-16 12:55:39','',0,'http://blog.iogrow.com/?p=55',0,'post','',0),(56,1,'2014-12-15 22:32:10','2014-12-15 22:32:10','<p class=\"post-title\">During your business life, you will meet some new interesting people who are potential customers in future; we call these people Leads.</p>\r\n\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">According to Leads360 s analysis of 25 million data points, speed is the single most critical component to lead conversion. Conversion rates are 391% higher when the lead is called within a minute of their inquiry; 120% within two minutes; 98% in under three minutes; 62% in under 30 minutes; and 36% in under an hour.\r\n\r\nReceiving and reacting to leads in real-time is critical to maximizing conversion rates. The companies that do this best measure reaction-time-to-new leads in seconds, not hours. By doing so, they achieve the first contact advantage with prospects.\r\n\r\nIOGrow provides you with full-detailed cards about your leads; you can see their phone number, email, address and even their social links. This will help you organize and keep tracking your leads so they can be qualified smoothly.\r\n\r\nA new qualified lead means a new customer contact or account. By converting your qualified leads into contacts, you will have all the information of your leads transferred to a new customer contact card instantly.\r\n\r\nOnce a Lead is qualified and determined to be a potential sale, the Lead can be converted to a Contact. A Company Account record will be created simultaneously to store the personal information and company information.\r\n\r\n</section>','Drop #13: Managing leads','','inherit','open','open','','55-revision-v1','','','2014-12-15 22:32:10','2014-12-15 22:32:10','',55,'http://blog.iogrow.com/55-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(57,1,'2014-12-15 22:43:49','2014-12-15 22:43:49','<h1 class=\"post-title\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Aug/Screen_Shot_2014_08_31_at_13_46_05.png\" alt=\"\" /></h1>\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">Emails are key to maintain strong customer relationships. We already know that it takes many emails to close a deal, in fact the majority of your customer conversations happen via email, IOGrow is here to help you keep all your conversations about an account, contact, lead or deal in one place. Using ioGrow, you can send Emails to your Contacts and Potential Leads.\r\n\r\nEvery update, news, conversation or opportunity is immediately shared with the appropriate contacts and accounts automatically.\r\n\r\nIOGrow built in email system offers you the possibility to receive emails and reply to customers internally, saving you the time and hassle of going out of IOGrow to your email client application.\r\n\r\nTo send an email from a specific record in ioGrow, make sure to do the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Select a record in your ioGrow homepage. (eg. Leads, Cases, Contacts, etc)</li>\r\n	<li>In the record show page, click the Send an Email tab.</li>\r\n	<li>From send an email page, you can choose the recipient, CC and/or BCC, the email subject and you can customize your email with a dedicated text editor, also you can insert link or insert images.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</section>','Drop #14: Email within ioGrow','','publish','open','open','','drop-14-email-within-iogrow','','','2014-12-15 22:43:49','2014-12-15 22:43:49','',0,'http://blog.iogrow.com/?p=57',0,'post','',0),(58,1,'2014-12-15 22:43:49','2014-12-15 22:43:49','<h1 class=\"post-title\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Aug/Screen_Shot_2014_08_31_at_13_46_05.png\" alt=\"\" /></h1>\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">Emails are key to maintain strong customer relationships. We already know that it takes many emails to close a deal, in fact the majority of your customer conversations happen via email, IOGrow is here to help you keep all your conversations about an account, contact, lead or deal in one place. Using ioGrow, you can send Emails to your Contacts and Potential Leads.\r\n\r\nEvery update, news, conversation or opportunity is immediately shared with the appropriate contacts and accounts automatically.\r\n\r\nIOGrow built in email system offers you the possibility to receive emails and reply to customers internally, saving you the time and hassle of going out of IOGrow to your email client application.\r\n\r\nTo send an email from a specific record in ioGrow, make sure to do the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Select a record in your ioGrow homepage. (eg. Leads, Cases, Contacts, etc)</li>\r\n	<li>In the record show page, click the Send an Email tab.</li>\r\n	<li>From send an email page, you can choose the recipient, CC and/or BCC, the email subject and you can customize your email with a dedicated text editor, also you can insert link or insert images.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</section>','Drop #14: Email within ioGrow','','inherit','open','open','','57-revision-v1','','','2014-12-15 22:43:49','2014-12-15 22:43:49','',57,'http://blog.iogrow.com/57-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(59,1,'2014-12-15 22:48:11','2014-12-15 22:48:11','<h1 class=\"post-title\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Aug/Screen_Shot_2014_08_31_at_13_36_08.png\" alt=\"\" /></h1>\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">Notes in CRM are as important as paper sticky notes in real life. We need notes to write phone numbers, information, questions, reminders, and anything you would write on notepaper. Notes in CRM are mainly used for visualizing information related to customers, accounts, tasks, leads, nearly everything, information that you may need later.\r\n\r\nIn ioGrow, notes tab is available in every record page, from Accounts, Contacts, Lead and even Opportunities; in every record, you can use notes to write customized, important information for each record. You can take notes by filling the subject and the notes itself also you can click on the note to edit it or to discuss or even delete it later.\r\n\r\nAnother important feature that ioGrow provides is the ability to attach documents from your Desktop or Google Docs to the account, leads, contacts, opportunity, etc..\r\n\r\nTo attach files to a specific record in ioGrow, you should do the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sign in to ioGrow using your Google account</li>\r\n	<li>Select a record in your ioGrow homepage. (eg. Leads, Cases, Contacts, etc).</li>\r\n	<li>In the record show page, click the Attach Documents tab.</li>\r\n	<li>You can choose whether you create a new file or upload from your Google Drive or from your Desktop.</li>\r\n	<li>Whether you are in Google Drive or Desktop choose the desired document and click Upload.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</section>','Drop #15: Attach documents & notes','','publish','open','open','','drop-15-attach-documents-notes','','','2014-12-15 22:48:11','2014-12-15 22:48:11','',0,'http://blog.iogrow.com/?p=59',0,'post','',0),(60,1,'2014-12-15 22:48:11','2014-12-15 22:48:11','<h1 class=\"post-title\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Aug/Screen_Shot_2014_08_31_at_13_36_08.png\" alt=\"\" /></h1>\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">Notes in CRM are as important as paper sticky notes in real life. We need notes to write phone numbers, information, questions, reminders, and anything you would write on notepaper. Notes in CRM are mainly used for visualizing information related to customers, accounts, tasks, leads, nearly everything, information that you may need later.\r\n\r\nIn ioGrow, notes tab is available in every record page, from Accounts, Contacts, Lead and even Opportunities; in every record, you can use notes to write customized, important information for each record. You can take notes by filling the subject and the notes itself also you can click on the note to edit it or to discuss or even delete it later.\r\n\r\nAnother important feature that ioGrow provides is the ability to attach documents from your Desktop or Google Docs to the account, leads, contacts, opportunity, etc..\r\n\r\nTo attach files to a specific record in ioGrow, you should do the following:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Sign in to ioGrow using your Google account</li>\r\n	<li>Select a record in your ioGrow homepage. (eg. Leads, Cases, Contacts, etc).</li>\r\n	<li>In the record show page, click the Attach Documents tab.</li>\r\n	<li>You can choose whether you create a new file or upload from your Google Drive or from your Desktop.</li>\r\n	<li>Whether you are in Google Drive or Desktop choose the desired document and click Upload.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</section>','Drop #15: Attach documents & notes','','inherit','open','open','','59-revision-v1','','','2014-12-15 22:48:11','2014-12-15 22:48:11','',59,'http://blog.iogrow.com/59-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(61,1,'2014-12-15 22:53:51','2014-12-15 22:53:51','ioGrow has been on a roll lately. Weve add so many new features and fixed more bugs. Today were excited to talk about one of the most requested features in ioGrow: CSV import, which means the ability of to import note, emails, contacts, cases, and deals.\r\n<p class=\"post-title\">Why its important for you?</p>\r\n\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">We all read about 37Signals\' announcement that they are no longer investing in Highrise, so if you are wondering what to do with your data, ioGrow is here opening its doors just for you.</section><section class=\"post-content\">\r\n<h5><!--more--></h5>\r\n<h5 id=\"howyoudoit\">How you do it?</h5>\r\n<h6 id=\"thisstepsofhowtomigratedatafromhighrisetoiogrow\">This steps of how to Migrate Data from HighRise to ioGrow.</h6>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Sign in to <strong>ioGrow.com</strong></li>\r\n	<li>Click <strong>Relationships</strong> at the top-left corner of your ioGrow page, then choose <strong>Admin Console</strong>.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_14_30_39.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"457\" height=\"231\" /></li>\r\n	<li>from the left menu choose <strong>Import</strong> then choose <strong>Highrise</strong>.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/iogrow_import_ui.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"849\" height=\"397\" />\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Enter your Key (API token) and your Server Name (Highrise Domain).\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/highrise_import_ui.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"835\" height=\"280\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nServer Name is the name of your Highrise account. Copy paste it from the address bar.\r\n\r\nFollow these steps to find the Key or API token in your Highrise account.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Login to your Highrise account.</li>\r\n	<li>Go to \"Account &amp; Settings\" on the top right corner.</li>\r\n	<li>Click on \"My Info\"</li>\r\n	<li>Choose \"API token\" from the tabs and there it is.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\nAfter you enter the Key and Server Name, just click the red button<strong>import</strong>. and Voila all your data are gently imported to <strong>ioGrow</strong>.\r\n\r\n</section>&nbsp;','Drop #16: Import data from HighRise to ioGrow.','','publish','open','open','','drop-16-import-data-from-highrise-to-iogrow','','','2014-12-19 20:01:00','2014-12-19 20:01:00','',0,'http://blog.iogrow.com/?p=61',0,'post','',0),(62,1,'2014-12-15 22:53:51','2014-12-15 22:53:51','<p class=\"post-title\">ioGrow has been on a roll lately. Weve add so many new features and fixed more bugs. Today were excited to talk about one of the most requested features in ioGrow: CSV import, which means the ability of to import note, emails, contacts, cases, and deals.</p>\r\n\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">\r\n<h5 id=\"whyitsimportantforyou\">Why its important for you?</h5>\r\nWe all read about 37Signals\' announcement that they are no longer investing in Highrise, so if you are wondering what to do with your data, ioGrow is here opening its doors just for you.\r\n<h5 id=\"howyoudoit\">How you do it?</h5>\r\n<h6 id=\"thisstepsofhowtomigratedatafromhighrisetoiogrow\">This steps of how to Migrate Data from HighRise to ioGrow.</h6>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Sign in to <strong>ioGrow.com</strong></li>\r\n	<li>Click <strong>Relationships</strong> at the top-left corner of your ioGrow page, then choose <strong>Admin Console</strong>.\r\n<img src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_14_30_39.png\" alt=\"\" /></li>\r\n	<li>from the left menu choose <strong>Import</strong> then choose <strong>Highrise</strong>.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<img src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/iogrow_import_ui.png\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Enter your Key (API token) and your Server Name (Highrise Domain).\r\n<img src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/highrise_import_ui.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nServer Name is the name of your Highrise account. Copy paste it from the address bar.\r\n\r\nFollow these steps to find the Key or API token in your Highrise account.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Login to your Highrise account.</li>\r\n	<li>Go to \"Account &amp; Settings\" on the top right corner.</li>\r\n	<li>Click on \"My Info\"</li>\r\n	<li>Choose \"API token\" from the tabs and there it is.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\nAfter you enter the Key and Server Name, just click the red button<strong>import</strong>. and Voila all your data are gently imported to <strong>ioGrow</strong>.\r\n\r\n</section>','Drop #16: Import data from HighRise to ioGrow.','','inherit','open','open','','61-revision-v1','','','2014-12-15 22:53:51','2014-12-15 22:53:51','',61,'http://blog.iogrow.com/61-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(63,1,'2014-12-15 22:57:45','2014-12-15 22:57:45','<p class=\"post-title\">To import contacts to ioGrow:</p>\r\n\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Create a custom CSV file, or export the address book from your other CRM or contacts manager as a CSV file.</li>\r\n	<li>Sign in to <strong>ioGrow.com</strong></li>\r\n	<li>From the main left menu choose <strong>Contacts</strong>.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" title=\"\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_08_13.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"335\" height=\"386\" />\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Then Click the Upload icon, next to New Contact button.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_26_46.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"824\" height=\"74\" />\r\n\r\n5 . After choose whether your CSV file is from Google Apps or Microsoft Outlook. and click <strong>Import</strong>.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_32_19.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"274\" />\r\n\r\n6 .Click the <strong>Select a file from your computer</strong> button.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_36_16.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"340\" height=\"195\" />Select the CSV file you\'d like to upload.\r\nWhen it\'s done, ioGrow will display the contacts imported.\r\n\r\n</section>&nbsp;','Drop #17: Import contacts as a CSV file','','publish','open','open','','drop-17-import-contacts-as-a-csv-file','','','2014-12-19 19:31:25','2014-12-19 19:31:25','',0,'http://blog.iogrow.com/?p=63',0,'post','',0),(64,1,'2014-12-15 22:54:49','2014-12-15 22:54:49','ioGrow has been on a roll lately. Weve add so many new features and fixed more bugs. Today were excited to talk about one of the most requested features in ioGrow: CSV import, which means the ability of to import note, emails, contacts, cases, and deals.\r\n<p class=\"post-title\">Why its important for you?</p>\r\n\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">We all read about 37Signals\' announcement that they are no longer investing in Highrise, so if you are wondering what to do with your data, ioGrow is here opening its doors just for you.\r\n<h5 id=\"howyoudoit\">How you do it?</h5>\r\n<h6 id=\"thisstepsofhowtomigratedatafromhighrisetoiogrow\">This steps of how to Migrate Data from HighRise to ioGrow.</h6>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Sign in to <strong>ioGrow.com</strong></li>\r\n	<li>Click <strong>Relationships</strong> at the top-left corner of your ioGrow page, then choose <strong>Admin Console</strong>.\r\n<img src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_14_30_39.png\" alt=\"\" /></li>\r\n	<li>from the left menu choose <strong>Import</strong> then choose <strong>Highrise</strong>.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<img src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/iogrow_import_ui.png\" alt=\"\" />\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Enter your Key (API token) and your Server Name (Highrise Domain).\r\n<img src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/highrise_import_ui.jpg\" alt=\"\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nServer Name is the name of your Highrise account. Copy paste it from the address bar.\r\n\r\nFollow these steps to find the Key or API token in your Highrise account.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Login to your Highrise account.</li>\r\n	<li>Go to \"Account &amp; Settings\" on the top right corner.</li>\r\n	<li>Click on \"My Info\"</li>\r\n	<li>Choose \"API token\" from the tabs and there it is.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\nAfter you enter the Key and Server Name, just click the red button<strong>import</strong>. and Voila all your data are gently imported to <strong>ioGrow</strong>.\r\n\r\n</section>','Drop #16: Import data from HighRise to ioGrow.','','inherit','open','open','','61-revision-v1','','','2014-12-15 22:54:49','2014-12-15 22:54:49','',61,'http://blog.iogrow.com/61-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(65,1,'2014-12-15 22:55:51','2014-12-15 22:55:51','ioGrow has been on a roll lately. Weve add so many new features and fixed more bugs. Today were excited to talk about one of the most requested features in ioGrow: CSV import, which means the ability of to import note, emails, contacts, cases, and deals.\n<p class=\"post-title\">Why its important for you?</p>\n\n<section class=\"post-content\">We all read about 37Signals\' announcement that they are no longer investing in Highrise, so if you are wondering what to do with your data, ioGrow is here opening its doors just for you.\n<h5 id=\"howyoudoit\">How you do it?</h5>\n<h6 id=\"thisstepsofhowtomigratedatafromhighrisetoiogrow\">This steps of how to Migrate Data from HighRise to ioGrow.</h6>\n<ol>\n	<li>Sign in to <strong>ioGrow.com</strong></li>\n	<li>Click <strong>Relationships</strong> at the top-left corner of your ioGrow page, then choose <strong>Admin Console</strong>.\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_14_30_39.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"457\" height=\"231\" /></li>\n	<li>from the left menu choose <strong>Import</strong> then choose <strong>Highrise</strong>.</li>\n</ol>\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/iogrow_import_ui.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"849\" height=\"397\" />\n<ol>\n	<li>Enter your Key (API token) and your Server Name (Highrise Domain).\n<img class=\"\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/highrise_import_ui.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"847\" height=\"284\" /></li>\n</ol>\nServer Name is the name of your Highrise account. Copy paste it from the address bar.\n\nFollow these steps to find the Key or API token in your Highrise account.\n<ul>\n	<li>Login to your Highrise account.</li>\n	<li>Go to \"Account &amp; Settings\" on the top right corner.</li>\n	<li>Click on \"My Info\"</li>\n	<li>Choose \"API token\" from the tabs and there it is.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<hr />\n\nAfter you enter the Key and Server Name, just click the red button<strong>import</strong>. and Voila all your data are gently imported to <strong>ioGrow</strong>.\n\n</section>','Drop #16: Import data from HighRise to ioGrow.','','inherit','open','open','','61-autosave-v1','','','2014-12-15 22:55:51','2014-12-15 22:55:51','',61,'http://blog.iogrow.com/61-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(66,1,'2014-12-15 22:56:00','2014-12-15 22:56:00','ioGrow has been on a roll lately. Weve add so many new features and fixed more bugs. Today were excited to talk about one of the most requested features in ioGrow: CSV import, which means the ability of to import note, emails, contacts, cases, and deals.\r\n<p class=\"post-title\">Why its important for you?</p>\r\n\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">We all read about 37Signals\' announcement that they are no longer investing in Highrise, so if you are wondering what to do with your data, ioGrow is here opening its doors just for you.\r\n<h5 id=\"howyoudoit\">How you do it?</h5>\r\n<h6 id=\"thisstepsofhowtomigratedatafromhighrisetoiogrow\">This steps of how to Migrate Data from HighRise to ioGrow.</h6>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Sign in to <strong>ioGrow.com</strong></li>\r\n	<li>Click <strong>Relationships</strong> at the top-left corner of your ioGrow page, then choose <strong>Admin Console</strong>.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_14_30_39.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"457\" height=\"231\" /></li>\r\n	<li>from the left menu choose <strong>Import</strong> then choose <strong>Highrise</strong>.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/iogrow_import_ui.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"849\" height=\"397\" />\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Enter your Key (API token) and your Server Name (Highrise Domain).\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/highrise_import_ui.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"835\" height=\"280\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nServer Name is the name of your Highrise account. Copy paste it from the address bar.\r\n\r\nFollow these steps to find the Key or API token in your Highrise account.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Login to your Highrise account.</li>\r\n	<li>Go to \"Account &amp; Settings\" on the top right corner.</li>\r\n	<li>Click on \"My Info\"</li>\r\n	<li>Choose \"API token\" from the tabs and there it is.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\nAfter you enter the Key and Server Name, just click the red button<strong>import</strong>. and Voila all your data are gently imported to <strong>ioGrow</strong>.\r\n\r\n</section>','Drop #16: Import data from HighRise to ioGrow.','','inherit','open','open','','61-revision-v1','','','2014-12-15 22:56:00','2014-12-15 22:56:00','',61,'http://blog.iogrow.com/61-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(67,1,'2014-12-15 22:57:45','2014-12-15 22:57:45','<p class=\"post-title\">To import contacts to ioGrow:</p>\r\n\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Create a custom CSV file, or export the address book from your other CRM or contacts manager as a CSV file.</li>\r\n	<li>Sign in to <strong>ioGrow.com</strong></li>\r\n	<li>From the main left menu choose <strong>Contacts</strong>.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" title=\"\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_08_13.png\" alt=\"\" /></li>\r\n	<li>Then Click the Upload icon, next to New Contact button.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_26_46.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"824\" height=\"74\" />\r\n\r\n5 . After choose whether your CSV file is from Google Apps or Microsoft Outlook. and click <strong>Import</strong>.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_32_19.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"803\" height=\"400\" />\r\n\r\n6 .Click the <strong>Select a file from your computer</strong> button.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_36_16.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"431\" height=\"247\" />Select the CSV file you\'d like to upload.\r\nWhen it\'s done, ioGrow will display the contacts imported.\r\n\r\n</section>','Drop #17: Import contacts as a CSV file','','inherit','open','open','','63-revision-v1','','','2014-12-15 22:57:45','2014-12-15 22:57:45','',63,'http://blog.iogrow.com/63-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(68,1,'2014-12-16 12:55:24','2014-12-16 12:55:24','During your business life, you will meet some new interesting people who are potential customers in future; we call these people Leads.\r\n\r\nAccording to Leads360 s analysis of 25 million data points, speed is the single most critical component to lead conversion. Conversion rates are 391% higher when the lead is called within a minute of their inquiry; 120% within two minutes; 98% in under three minutes; 62% in under 30 minutes; and 36% in under an hour.\r\n\r\nReceiving and reacting to leads in real-time is critical to maximizing conversion rates. The companies that do this best measure reaction-time-to-new leads in seconds, not hours. By doing so, they achieve the first contact advantage with prospects.\r\nIOGrow provides you with full-detailed cards about your leads; you can see their phone number, email, address and even their social links. This will help you organize and keep tracking your leads so they can be qualified smoothly.\r\n\r\nA new qualified lead means a new customer contact or account. By converting your qualified leads into contacts, you will have all the information of your leads transferred to a new customer contact card instantly.\r\n\r\nOnce a Lead is qualified and determined to be a potential sale, the Lead can be converted to a Contact. A Company Account record will be created simultaneously to store the personal information and company information.','Drop #13: Managing leads','','inherit','open','open','','55-autosave-v1','','','2014-12-16 12:55:24','2014-12-16 12:55:24','',55,'http://blog.iogrow.com/55-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(69,1,'2014-12-16 12:54:50','2014-12-16 12:54:50','During your business life, you will meet some new interesting people who are potential customers in future; we call these people Leads.\r\n<p class=\"post-title\">According to Leads360 s analysis of 25 million data points, speed is the single most critical component to lead conversion. Conversion rates are 391% higher when the lead is called within a minute of their inquiry; 120% within two minutes; 98% in under three minutes; 62% in under 30 minutes; and 36% in under an hour.</p>\r\n\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">Receiving and reacting to leads in real-time is critical to maximizing conversion rates. The companies that do this best measure reaction-time-to-new leads in seconds, not hours. By doing so, they achieve the first contact advantage with prospects.\r\n\r\nIOGrow provides you with full-detailed cards about your leads; you can see their phone number, email, address and even their social links. This will help you organize and keep tracking your leads so they can be qualified smoothly.\r\n\r\nA new qualified lead means a new customer contact or account. By converting your qualified leads into contacts, you will have all the information of your leads transferred to a new customer contact card instantly.\r\n\r\nOnce a Lead is qualified and determined to be a potential sale, the Lead can be converted to a Contact. A Company Account record will be created simultaneously to store the personal information and company information.\r\n\r\n</section>','Drop #13: Managing leads','','inherit','open','open','','55-revision-v1','','','2014-12-16 12:54:50','2014-12-16 12:54:50','',55,'http://blog.iogrow.com/55-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(70,1,'2014-12-16 12:55:39','2014-12-16 12:55:39','During your business life, you will meet some new interesting people who are potential customers in future; we call these people Leads.\r\n\r\nAccording to Leads360 s analysis of 25 million data points, speed is the single most critical component to lead conversion. Conversion rates are 391% higher when the lead is called within a minute of their inquiry; 120% within two minutes; 98% in under three minutes; 62% in under 30 minutes; and 36% in under an hour.\r\n\r\nReceiving and reacting to leads in real-time is critical to maximizing conversion rates. The companies that do this best measure reaction-time-to-new leads in seconds, not hours. By doing so, they achieve the first contact advantage with prospects.\r\nIOGrow provides you with full-detailed cards about your leads; you can see their phone number, email, address and even their social links. This will help you organize and keep tracking your leads so they can be qualified smoothly.\r\n\r\nA new qualified lead means a new customer contact or account. By converting your qualified leads into contacts, you will have all the information of your leads transferred to a new customer contact card instantly.\r\n\r\nOnce a Lead is qualified and determined to be a potential sale, the Lead can be converted to a Contact. A Company Account record will be created simultaneously to store the personal information and company information.','Drop #13: Managing leads','','inherit','open','open','','55-revision-v1','','','2014-12-16 12:55:39','2014-12-16 12:55:39','',55,'http://blog.iogrow.com/55-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(71,1,'2014-12-16 13:23:18','2014-12-16 13:23:18','','Auto Draft','','trash','open','open','','auto-draft','','','2014-12-16 13:23:34','2014-12-16 13:23:34','',0,'http://blog.iogrow.com/?post_type=kes_campaign&#038;p=71',0,'kes_campaign','',0),(72,1,'2014-12-16 13:32:20','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','','','draft','closed','closed','','','','','2014-12-16 13:32:20','2014-12