blog.iogrow.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/ticket1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(107,1,'2014-12-17 19:53:32','2014-12-17 19:53:32','','tie (1)','','inherit','open','open','','tie-1-2','','','2014-12-17 19:53:32','2014-12-17 19:53:32','',0,'http://blog.iogrow.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/tie-11.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(108,1,'2014-12-17 19:53:33','2014-12-17 19:53:33','','tie','','inherit','open','open','','tie-2','','','2014-12-17 19:53:33','2014-12-17 19:53:33','',0,'http://blog.iogrow.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/tie1.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(109,1,'2014-12-17 22:51:51','2014-12-17 22:51:51','','chrome tab logo iogroqw','','inherit','open','open','','chrome-tab-logo-iogroqw','','','2014-12-17 22:51:51','2014-12-17 22:51:51','',0,'http://blog.iogrow.com/wp-content/uploads/2014/12/chrome-tab-logo-iogroqw.png',0,'attachment','image/png',0),(110,1,'2014-12-19 18:32:12','2014-12-19 18:32:12','<h1 class=\"post-title\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Aug/Screen_Shot_2014_08_31_at_11_07_13.png\" alt=\"\" /></h1>\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">Cards are quickly becoming one the best user interfaces design pattern for both desktop and mobile devices.\r\nWe at ioGrow are adopting cards design, away from pages, towards a completely personalised experience built on an aggregation of many individual pieces of content.Cards are perfect for mobile devices and varying screen sizes. Remember, mobile devices are the heart and soul of the future of your business, no matter who you are and what you do. On mobile devices, cards can be stacked vertically, like an activity stream on a phone.\r\n\r\nWe think there is no getting away from it. Cards are the next big thing in design and the creative arts. To us thats incredibly exciting.\r\n\r\nNext up, make sure to check out:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Manage Leads (Post TBA)</li>\r\n	<li>Manage Contacts (Post TBA)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nHappy reading!\r\n\r\n</section>','Drop #7: Minimalistic cards design','','inherit','open','open','','37-revision-v1','','','2014-12-19 18:32:12','2014-12-19 18:32:12','',37,'http://blog.iogrow.com/37-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(111,1,'2014-12-19 18:34:12','2014-12-19 18:34:12','<h1 class=\"post-title\"><img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Aug/Screen_Shot_2014_08_31_at_11_07_13.png\" alt=\"\" /></h1>\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">Cards are quickly becoming one the best user interfaces design pattern for both desktop and mobile devices.\r\nWe at ioGrow are adopting cards design, away from pages, towards a completely personalised experience built on an aggregation of many individual pieces of content.Cards are perfect for mobile devices and varying screen sizes. Remember, mobile devices are the heart and soul of the future of your business, no matter who you are and what you do. On mobile devices, cards can be stacked vertically, like an activity stream on a phone.We think there is no getting away from it. Cards are the next big thing in design and the creative arts. To us thats incredibly exciting.\r\n\r\nNext up, make sure to check out:\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Manage Leads (Post TBA)</li>\r\n	<li>Manage Contacts (Post TBA)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nHappy reading!\r\n\r\n</section>','Drop #7: Minimalistic cards design','','inherit','open','open','','37-revision-v1','','','2014-12-19 18:34:12','2014-12-19 18:34:12','',37,'http://blog.iogrow.com/37-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(112,1,'2014-12-19 19:04:01','2014-12-19 19:04:01','<p class=\"post-title\">To import contacts to ioGrow:</p>\r\n\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Create a custom CSV file, or export the address book from your other CRM or contacts manager as a CSV file.</li>\r\n	<li>Sign in to <strong>ioGrow.com</strong></li>\r\n	<li>From the main left menu choose <strong>Contacts</strong>.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" title=\"\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_08_13.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"335\" height=\"386\" /></li>\r\n	<li>Then Click the Upload icon, next to New Contact button.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_26_46.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"824\" height=\"74\" />\r\n\r\n5 . After choose whether your CSV file is from Google Apps or Microsoft Outlook. and click <strong>Import</strong>.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_32_19.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"274\" />\r\n\r\n6 .Click the <strong>Select a file from your computer</strong> button.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_36_16.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"340\" height=\"195\" />Select the CSV file you\'d like to upload.\r\nWhen it\'s done, ioGrow will display the contacts imported.\r\n\r\n</section><!--more-->','Drop #17: Import contacts as a CSV file','','inherit','open','open','','63-revision-v1','','','2014-12-19 19:04:01','2014-12-19 19:04:01','',63,'http://blog.iogrow.com/63-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(113,1,'2014-12-19 19:30:18','2014-12-19 19:30:18','<p class=\"post-title\">To import contacts to ioGrow:</p>\r\n\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Create a custom CSV file, or export the address book from your other CRM or contacts manager as a CSV file.</li>\r\n	<li>Sign in to <strong>ioGrow.com</strong></li>\r\n	<li>From the main left menu choose <strong>Contacts</strong>.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" title=\"\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_08_13.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"335\" height=\"386\" />\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Then Click the Upload icon, next to New Contact button.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_26_46.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"824\" height=\"74\" />\r\n\r\n5 . After choose whether your CSV file is from Google Apps or Microsoft Outlook. and click <strong>Import</strong>.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_32_19.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"274\" />\r\n\r\n6 .Click the <strong>Select a file from your computer</strong> button.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_36_16.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"340\" height=\"195\" />Select the CSV file you\'d like to upload.\r\nWhen it\'s done, ioGrow will display the contacts imported.\r\n\r\n</section><!--more-->\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<!--more-->','Drop #17: Import contacts as a CSV file','','inherit','open','open','','63-revision-v1','','','2014-12-19 19:30:18','2014-12-19 19:30:18','',63,'http://blog.iogrow.com/63-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(114,1,'2014-12-19 19:31:23','2014-12-19 19:31:23','<p class=\"post-title\">To import contacts to ioGrow:</p>\n\n<section class=\"post-content\">\n<ol>\n	<li>Create a custom CSV file, or export the address book from your other CRM or contacts manager as a CSV file.</li>\n	<li>Sign in to <strong>ioGrow.com</strong></li>\n	<li>From the main left menu choose <strong>Contacts</strong>.</li>\n</ol>\n<!--more-->\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" title=\"\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_08_13.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"335\" height=\"386\" />\n<ol>\n	<li>Then Click the Upload icon, next to New Contact button.</li>\n</ol>\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_26_46.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"824\" height=\"74\" />\n\n5 . After choose whether your CSV file is from Google Apps or Microsoft Outlook. and click <strong>Import</strong>.\n\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_32_19.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"274\" />\n\n6 .Click the <strong>Select a file from your computer</strong> button.\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_36_16.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"340\" height=\"195\" />Select the CSV file you\'d like to upload.\nWhen it\'s done, ioGrow will display the contacts imported.\n\n</section>&nbsp;','Drop #17: Import contacts as a CSV file','','inherit','open','open','','63-autosave-v1','','','2014-12-19 19:31:23','2014-12-19 19:31:23','',63,'http://blog.iogrow.com/63-autosave-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(115,1,'2014-12-19 19:31:25','2014-12-19 19:31:25','<p class=\"post-title\">To import contacts to ioGrow:</p>\r\n\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Create a custom CSV file, or export the address book from your other CRM or contacts manager as a CSV file.</li>\r\n	<li>Sign in to <strong>ioGrow.com</strong></li>\r\n	<li>From the main left menu choose <strong>Contacts</strong>.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<!--more-->\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" title=\"\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_08_13.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"335\" height=\"386\" />\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Then Click the Upload icon, next to New Contact button.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_26_46.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"824\" height=\"74\" />\r\n\r\n5 . After choose whether your CSV file is from Google Apps or Microsoft Outlook. and click <strong>Import</strong>.\r\n\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_32_19.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"550\" height=\"274\" />\r\n\r\n6 .Click the <strong>Select a file from your computer</strong> button.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_17_36_16.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"340\" height=\"195\" />Select the CSV file you\'d like to upload.\r\nWhen it\'s done, ioGrow will display the contacts imported.\r\n\r\n</section>&nbsp;','Drop #17: Import contacts as a CSV file','','inherit','open','open','','63-revision-v1','','','2014-12-19 19:31:25','2014-12-19 19:31:25','',63,'http://blog.iogrow.com/63-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(116,1,'2014-12-19 19:43:21','2014-12-19 19:43:21','ioGrow has been on a roll lately. Weve add so many new features and fixed more bugs. Today were excited to talk about one of the most requested features in ioGrow: CSV import, which means the ability of to import note, emails, contacts, cases, and deals.\r\n<p class=\"post-title\">Why its important for you?</p>\r\n\r\n<section class=\"post-content\">We all read about 37Signals\' announcement that they are no longer investing in Highrise, so if you are wondering what to do with your data, ioGrow is here opening its doors just for you.</section><section class=\"post-content\">\r\n<h5><!--more--></h5>\r\n<h5 id=\"howyoudoit\">How you do it?</h5>\r\n<h6 id=\"thisstepsofhowtomigratedatafromhighrisetoiogrow\">This steps of how to Migrate Data from HighRise to ioGrow.</h6>\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Sign in to <strong>ioGrow.com</strong></li>\r\n	<li>Click <strong>Relationships</strong> at the top-left corner of your ioGrow page, then choose <strong>Admin Console</strong>.\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/Screenshot_2014_09_29_at_14_30_39.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"457\" height=\"231\" /></li>\r\n	<li>from the left menu choose <strong>Import</strong> then choose <strong>Highrise</strong>.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/iogrow_import_ui.png\" alt=\"\" width=\"849\" height=\"397\" />\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Enter your Key (API token) and your Server Name (Highrise Domain).\r\n<img class=\"aligncenter\" src=\"http://iogrowblog.azurewebsites.net/content/images/2014/Sep/highrise_import_ui.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"835\" height=\"280\" /></li>\r\n</ol>\r\nServer Name is the name of your Highrise account. Copy paste it from the address bar.\r\n\r\nFollow these steps to find the Key or API token in your Highrise account.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Login to your Highrise account.</li>\r\n	<li>Go to \"Account &amp; Settings\" on the top right corner.</li>\r\n	<li>Click on \"My Info\"</li>\r\n	<li>Choose \"API token\" from the tabs and there it is.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n\r\nAfter you enter the Key and Server Name, just click the red button<strong>import</strong>. and Voila all your data are gently imported to <strong>ioGrow</strong>.\r\n\r\n</section>&nbsp;','Drop #16: Import data from HighRise to ioGrow.','','inherit','open','open','','61-revision-v1','','','2014-12-19 19:43:21','2014-12-19 19:43:21','',61,'http://blog.iogrow.com/61-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(117,1,'2014-12-19 20:23:03','0000-00-00 00:00:00','','Auto Draft','','auto-draft','open','open','','','','','2014-12-19 20:23:03','0000-00-00 00:00:00','',0,'http://blog.iogrow.com/?p=117',0,'post','',0);
